parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can lead to a loss of stopping power, especially at low speeds, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail to provide stopping power at low speeds (6-7 mph and below)
accompanied by a loud retching noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or die, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly dies or stalls while driving
often at high speeds (45-50 mph)
and may not restart; repeated failures of the fuel pump and fuel pressure regulator; difficulty starting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck or hesitant
the vehicle surges or lurches forward unexpectedly
the engine RPM increases suddenly
the vehicle accelerates without input from the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Uneven tire wear
vibration while driving
loud noise while driving
tire blowout
tire chunks or pieces coming off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tailgate cables can cause the tailgate to fall suddenly, potentially leading to injury or damage to the vehicle or surrounding objects.
symptoms: The tailgate cable snaps or breaks
the tailgate feels unstable or wobbly
the tailgate falls suddenly when opened or loaded
the tailgate is held up by only one cable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to lose power while driving, especially at high speeds, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or stalls while driving
the engine sputters or hesitates
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the vehicle cannot restart after stalling
the vehicle requires towing.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Fuel Pump Diagnosis and Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships or repair shops to properly diagnose and repair fuel pump issues can lead to repeated failures, causing inconvenience, danger, and financial losses to vehicle owners.
symptoms: The dealership or repair shop is unable to recreate the problem
the dealership or repair shop fails to diagnose the issue correctly
the dealership or repair shop fails to repair the issue effectively
the vehicle owner experiences repeated failures.
